item.title: TensorFlow.js Quick Start Tutorial
item.description: Google launched TensorFlow.js at TensorFlow Dev Summit 2018, which opens the door to building machine learning (ML) models in the browser. This means web developers can do things like… Build privacy-friendly AI features. Data never leaves the client, so you can build deep learning models without ever seeing the actual data. Use pre-trained Python ML models in your app. There are tons of successful Python-based models that you can load into the browser and start running predictions with minimal code.
